  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Right now, we maintain the `latestState`, which is the state after processing the latest received block. We're always using this to progress the chain.\r\nThis means we cannot process legitimate blocks that are not descendants of the latest block we've seen.\r\n\r\neg:\r\n```\r\nblock A -----> block B\r\n         \\\r\n          \\\r\n           \\\r\n            \\\r\n             > block C\r\n```\r\nIf we receive block C after processing block B, we currently cannot process it, since we're not using the state at block A, only using the new `latestState` (post-block B).\r\n\r\nWe should instead fetch the (non-latest) state needed to process a block if we need to.",
